update `instructions` set `title` = 'Laravel TinyMCE editor', `description` = '

TinyMCE 6 is a powerful and flexible rich text editor that can be embedded in web applications. This quick start covers how to add a TinyMCE editor to a web page using npm or Yarn. edit

\n

Credits

', `instructions`.`updated_at` = '2024-02-02 23:48:51' where `id` = '11'

v-model="snippetForm.description"
api-key="API_KEY"

    height: 200,
    plugins: 'lists link code wordcount codesample',
    toolbar: 'codesample | bold italic backcolor | \ bullist link'
}"
/>
